Project_description: The City of Richmond proposes to construct the Richmond-Greenway Gap Closure Project, a multi-use trail connection in Richmond, California. The Richmond-Ohlone Greenway Gap Closure Project represents the third phase of the Richmond Greenway Project, which would provide a continuous bicycle and pedestrian pathway in Richmond from Garrard Boulevard and the Richmond Parkway to San Pablo Avenue. The Richmond Greenway would connect the San Francisco Bay Trail at the west with the Ohlone Greenway in the City of El Cerrito at the east. The proposed project includes installation of the new multi-use trail, a new crosswalk and traffic signal on San Pablo Avenue, and a new bridge over realigned Baxter Creek as well as associated improvements and landscaping.

Project_description: The City of Eureka’s Five-Year Capital Improvement Program (CIP) is a multi-year planning instrument used to identify needed capital improvement projects and to coordinate the financing and timing of these improvements. The primary purpose of the CIP is to assist in the orderly implementation of the broad and comprehensive goals of the City’s adopted General Plan. The CIP also aids with planning for maintenance and replacement of the City's infrastructure by establishing an orderly basis to guide local officials in making sound budget decisions. Attention is also focused on community goals, needs, and capabilities to maximize the benefit of public expenditures.

The SeeClickFix Elk Grove app makes reporting a non-emergency problem easier than ever. This free app is a great way for residents of Elk Grove to report issues in the community as soon as they are discovered. This app uses GPS to recognize your location and gives you a menu of common quality-of-life conditions to report a problem. It allows you to upload pictures or videos to accompany your request and gives you the ability to track the issue from the time reported through resolution. The app can be used for a variety of requests such as street maintenance, streetlight requests, damaged trees, abandoned cars, code enforcement issues and more. The City of Elk Grove appreciates your feedback, and use of this software will allow us to improve and beautify our community.
